To ensure the safety and proper regulation of the customary practice, and in co-operation with the CRL Rights Commission, the Gauteng municipalities are well aware and informed on the conditions under which the municipalities are to host customary initiation. These conditions include: - To ensure that by-laws are in place; - Identify land where customary initiation can be practiced; - Municipalities must ensure that they create a database of initiation schools operating within their areas of jurisdiction; - Regular monitoring reports must be provided to CoGTA during the initiation season; - Water and sanitation must be provided at the sites allocated for customary initiation; - Municipalities are to ensure that initiates have access to medical screening before they participate in an initiation school; and - Municipalities must enhance their application process.